/F1 11 Tf
72 750 Td
(Introduction to Retrieval-Augmented Generation \(RAG\)) Tj
72 735 Td
() Tj
72 720 Td
(RAG is a technique that combines retrieval-based and generative AI methods.) Tj
72 705 Td
(It first retrieves relevant documents from a knowledge base, then passes) Tj
72 690 Td
(them to a large language model \(LLM\) to generate a grounded answer.) Tj
72 675 Td
() Tj
72 660 Td
(Key Components:) Tj
72 645 Td
(1. Document Ingestion: PDFs are split into overlapping text chunks.) Tj
72 630 Td
(2. Embedding: Each chunk is encoded as a dense vector using a model) Tj
72 615 Td
(   such as BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5 from sentence-transformers.) Tj
72 600 Td
(3. Vector Store: Embeddings are stored in a FAISS or Chroma index) Tj
72 585 Td
(   for fast approximate nearest-neighbour search.) Tj
72 570 Td
(4. BM25 Sparse Retrieval: Keyword-based retrieval complements dense search.) Tj
72 555 Td
(5. Hybrid Retrieval: Dense and sparse scores are combined \(0.6 / 0.4 weights\).) Tj
72 540 Td
(6. Cross-Encoder Reranking: A cross-encoder model re-scores the top candidates) Tj
72 525 Td
(   and returns only the top-5 most relevant chunks to the LLM.) Tj
72 510 Td
(7. LLM Generation: The reranked chunks are injected into the LLM prompt.) Tj
72 495 Td
(   The model \(e.g. Mistral-7B-Instruct\) then generates the final answer.) Tj
72 480 Td
() Tj
72 465 Td
(Advantages of RAG:) Tj
72 450 Td
(- Reduces hallucinations by grounding answers in retrieved evidence.) Tj
72 435 Td
(- Allows knowledge updates without expensive model retraining.) Tj
72 420 Td
(- Source attribution is possible because the retrieved chunks are known.) Tj
72 405 Td
() Tj
72 390 Td
(Evaluation Metrics:) Tj
72 375 Td
(- Faithfulness: Does the answer stay true to the retrieved context?) Tj
72 360 Td
(- Answer Relevance: Does the answer address the user question?) Tj
72 345 Td
(- Context Recall: Were the most relevant chunks actually retrieved?) Tj
72 330 Td
() Tj
72 315 Td
(This project uses Hugging Face models exclusively, running the embedding) Tj
72 300 Td
(and reranking locally while optionally calling the Inference API for the LLM.) Tj
ET

